latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Bend it like Beckham turns 20yrs old, @brooklynpeltzbeckham gets married - @davidbeckham is a father in a law and I’m still as crazy as I was when I was 13 years old. 

I watched #BendItLikeBeckham for the first time when I was maybe 9 years old, and fell in love with not just #DavidBeckham but the game as well. 

It’s been twenty odd years of the greatest love story of my life - both with Beckham (one sided) and football.

Jess Bhamra you will have my heart forever - thank you @gurinder.chadha for this gem. It never gets old, and it always always inspires me to chase my dreams and goals!

Leaving you with a little crazy memory - from at least 16 years ago ...

Hi @dishchops, remember this? 😂💁🏼‍♀️
Decorate your Tree and Life just the way YOU want to. Merry Christmas y’all 🎄♥️

This is not an ad, well technically it is but @amazondotin didn’t pay me to promote it.

I just got it on WhatsApp, and it struck a chord like no other, watch it if you have two minutes. The most beautiful thing I have seen this year. Reminds me of some of the toughest times we saw, but also of the triumph of humanity & kindness like no other. 

Happy Diwali to the family I have never met, to all the usernames I might recognise and some that I might not. Happy Diwali to all of us, who stood by each other even from far away as we floated through the toughest crisis of our lives, through those scary nights and frightening days. Thank you for standing by me, helping me, doing things for me as you would for your kin. 
To the friends I made, to the ones we lost. To us all. 

I hope this Diwali will only bring in brighter and happier times, and to the ones we lost - it’ll never be the same without you. 🤍💫🪔

Also I hope everybody’s stay safe. 

Thanks for sharing this @rehmatbhasin and to the family I found @akritikhosla @tarinimanchanda @manatlkapur @jayatimodi @sukriti.sharrma @noorsethi @sanjrishi @mehrsingh96 @arshi_m @anntal @akshitasekhri @karimehta05 @keertikataria @amrita_thakur @aishwaryaaa_singhh @harteerathsingh and each and every single one of you - you know who you are!

latestIgtvVideos.title: I made a Beauty Video
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Don’t think I’ll ever do one again (how effortless & fab does everybody else look making one).

But literally just used @simplynam.beauty’s Reusable Makeup-Removing Towel by @namratasoni after a long day of shooting and man it really worked.

This is not a paid promotion a though the towel did come to me as a press gift (also the video is unedited) – so I would let you decide.

Though if you’re in Delhi (or anywhere cold) like me (and lazy) GET THIS! I sat in bed and removed it and also wasn’t guilty of using wipes (this is sustainable and can be used for upto 100 washes)

Damn Nam - this is simply awesome

latestPosts.caption:
One thing I’m deeply proud of is my ability to build community. I genuinely believe it’s in my DNA—I’ve grown up surrounded by it. My great-grandparents, my grandmother, and my parents have always been people who brought others together. Our home was constantly filled with friends, family, and visitors from across the globe. My grandmother, in particular, had a remarkable gift for staying connected, no matter the distance. I’ve been to cities where people have welcomed us with open arms purely because of the relationships she nurtured—and that spirit of connection has stayed with me.

This sense of community is something I’ve carried into my work as well. There’s something incredibly powerful and joyful about bringing people together, watching them form new bonds, and creating space for shared purpose and celebration.

At @bazaarindia , this came to life most meaningfully with the launch of Bazaar Dialogues. It filled me with pride to bring such a dynamic group of South Asians into one room—to share stories, celebrate our work and achievements, and simply be present together in that moment of collective recognition.

A heartfelt thank you to my partners @thebicestercollection (@dailysabahlife @tanyakrot @longformgram @shaina_rasul @pareinathapar), who supported my vision from the start and helped bring it to life. 
To our six incredible panelists (@shalinimisraltd @krishna_ch @yogesh.jaipurrugs @dhruvkapoor @nikhilmansata @iamdeepkailey) —thank you for making time despite your packed schedules. To old friends, new ones, and family who showed up to support—it meant the world (some in the photos and some who were out shopping at the village before I got around to photos haha) 
And to my incredible team back home and with me, who worked tirelessly on every detail—this wouldn’t have happened without you!

At #BazaarIndia, we look forward to continuing to foster meaningful conversations, amplifying diverse voices, and building a community that not only thrives together—but celebrates both the highs and the journeys in between.

Ps: thank you @sakshi.kohli for continuously pushing me, and making me wear the big girl boots ♥️
